[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ## CVE-2019-11043 Assessment                                                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m CVE-2019-11043 is a **critical remote code execution vulnerability** in      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m PHP-FPM (FastCGI Process Manager) that allows attackers to execute arbitrary [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m code by sending crafted requests containing newline characters (`%0a`) that  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m corrupt the FPM configuration.                                               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
